headline: 1 Ultra-High-Yield Dividend Stock You Won't Regret Buying in February
summary: Investing in higher-yielding dividend stocks has its benefits and drawbacks.  The risk of a dividend cut isn't something that Realty Income (NYSE: O) investors need to worry about.  Instead, the high-yielding (5.8% current yield) real estate investment trust (REIT) should be able to continue its impressive streak of increasing its dividend.

headline: 2 Stocks That Cut You a Check Each Month
summary: One of the best parts about investing is dividend income.  If you're looking for monthly dividend stocks, keep reading to see two attractive buys right now.  If you're looking for a dividend stock, a great place to start is with Realty Income (NYSE: O), a real estate investment trust (REIT) that currently pays a dividend yield of 5.7%.

headline: Like High-Yield Realty Income Stock? You May Like Alpine Even More.
summary: Realty Income (NYSE: O) is roughly 4 times the size of its next closest peer in the net lease niche of the real estate investment trust (REIT) sector.  There are a lot of things to like about this industry giant.  One at the opposite extreme, size-wise, is Alpine Income Property Trust (NYSE: PINE), one of the smallest net lease REITs you can buy.
